modules.description: Generates C stubs for OCaml foreign function interfaces based on provided configurations. It processes a list of configuration values that specify binding details, concurrency policies, and header files. Useful for automatically creating C glue code when interfacing OCaml with C libraries.

This module defines a function `rules` that generates build rules for Ctypes-based OCaml projects. It configures paths for bindings, libraries, and platform-specific directories, enabling integration of C libraries with OCaml code. Use it to automate compilation and linking of foreign function interfaces in MirageOS or similar systems.
